    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> So far so good, except I am stuck on the part where you show loading whenever the query is running.\r\n\r\nCould you detail a bit more \"where you show loading whenever the query is running\" => do you mean there's a documentation page where we show an interface displaying a \"loading\" mechanism and you do not understand how it works or smg else?\r\n\r\nWe do have a guide that explains how to read the search state: https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/guides/conditional-display.html\r\n\r\nAnd the state shape: https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/guides/create-own-widget.html#getpropsprops-state-search-meta\r\n\r\nBut we have to make it better.\r\n\r\nHere's an example:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst Loading = createConnector({\r\n    displayName: 'Loading',\r\n    getProps(props, state, search) {\r\n      return {loading: search.searching};\r\n    },\r\n })(({loading}) => {\r\n  console.log(loading);\r\n });\r\n```",
